# Project Status Tracking — Mandatory Workflow

`docs/SSOT/PROJECT_STATUS.md` is the **execution-state SSOT**. Every agent (human or AI) that adds, fixes, or modifies a feature MUST keep it in sync.

## Before you start any feature work

1. **Read** `docs/SSOT/PROJECT_STATUS.md` — confirm the feature isn't already done, and pick the highest-priority pending item per §2 if no specific feature was assigned.
2. **Read** the matching `FR-*` requirement in `docs/SSOT/SRS/02_functional_requirements/`.
3. **Move** the feature in §2 from `⏳ Planned` → `🟡 In progress` and update §3 (Sprint Board).

## While working

- If you discover technical debt outside scope, append `[PENDING REFACTOR]` to §6 of `PROJECT_STATUS.md` (and to `docs/SSOT/CODE_QUALITY.md` once it exists). Do not refactor inline.
- If a product/architecture decision is made on the fly, append it to §5 (and mirror to `SRS/appendices/C_decisions_log.md`).

## Before you call the work done

You MUST update `docs/SSOT/PROJECT_STATUS.md` in the same change-set as your code:

1. **§2 Backlog**: flip the status to `🟢 Done` (or `🟡 In progress` if partial).
2. **§4 Completed Features Log**: append a new entry at the top with:
   - SRS IDs covered + PRD anchor
   - Completed date (ISO)
   - Branch / commit ref
   - Files added / changed
   - Tests run + result
   - AC checklist verified
   - Known gaps deferred (with backlog priority band)
3. **§1 Snapshot**: bump `Last Updated`, completion %, counters.
4. **§3 Sprint Board**: clear the in-progress slot, set "Up next" to the new highest-priority pending item.

## Verification gate (already enforced by user rules)

Every code-bearing response must prefix:

```
Mapped to SRS: [Requirement ID]. Refactor logged: [Yes/No/NA].
```

## What "touching a feature" means

Any of:
- Creating new domain/application/infrastructure code that maps to an `FR-*`.
- Editing a screen, hook, or store tied to an `FR-*`.
- Replacing mock data with real repository calls.
- Fixing a defect in a feature already listed in §4.
- Adding tests that change the AC-verified set for a feature.

## What does NOT need a status update

- Pure tooling changes (CI config, linter rules, dependency bumps with no behavior change).
- Documentation-only edits to `SRS/`, `PRD_MVP_SSOT_/`, or this rule.
- Hotfixes that don't change any AC of an `FR-*`.

## Quick template for §4 entry

```markdown
### ✅ FR-XXX-NNN — <short title>

| Field | Value |
| ----- | ----- |
| Mapped to SRS | FR-XXX-NNN |
| PRD anchor | `0X_File.md` §X.Y |
| Completed | YYYY-MM-DD |
| Branch / commit | <ref> |
| Files added | ... |
| Files changed | ... |
| Tech debt logged | TD-N (see §6) |
| Tests | <command> — <result> |
| AC verified | AC1–AC<n> |
| Known gaps | <pointer to backlog band> |
```

## If you cannot update PROJECT_STATUS.md

Stop. Either you don't have write access, the feature isn't tracked, or scope is unclear. Surface the issue to the user before proceeding — do not silently skip the update.
